FBIS4-4197 "drchi083_d_94009" FBIS-CHI-94-083 Daily Report 29 Apr 1994 Northeast Asia Cooperation Accords Signed Cooperation Accords Signed OW2904090594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0805 GMT 29 Apr 94 OW2904090594 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 29 (XINHUA) -- China and Mongolia signed a range of documents on bilateral cooperation here today, shortly before Chinese Premier Li Peng wound up a two-day official visit to this country. The documents include agreements on the protection and utilization of water in border areas, on cultural cooperation, on cooperation in quarantine of animals and veterinary work, on economic and technological cooperation, on guarantee and mutual attestation of the quality of import and export commodities and on China's provision of aid to Mongolia. Both sides also signed an exchange of notes on border trade, and another such document on clearing up the remaining surplus in trade balance that occurred before the two countries introduced cash payment of developing bilateral trade.
